H0.text: What traditionally mysterious, increasingly transparent organization is casually referred to as 'The Craft'. The Rosicrucians

H1.text: What traditionally mysterious, increasingly transparent organization is casually referred to as 'The Craft'. The O.T.O. (Ordo Templi Orientis)

H2.text: What traditionally mysterious, increasingly transparent organization is casually referred to as 'The Craft'. The Golden Dawn

H3.text: What traditionally mysterious, increasingly transparent organization is casually referred to as 'The Craft'. AF&AM

A4.text: Its members claimed that the leaders of the Rosicrucian Order had invented Freemasonry and only they knew the secret meaning of Masonic symbols.

A5.text: The Hermetic Order of the Golden Dawn was derived from Societas Rosicruciana in Anglia and counted many prominent figures among its members.
